How to Install Python 2.7 on a Redhat 6 Machine in a go 
Create repo file 
#touch /etc/yum.repos.d/scl.repo
Download the repo file from redhat and copy the content to the scl.repo file you just created 
sudo sh -c 'wget -qO- http://people.redhat.com/bkabrda/scl_python27.repo >> /etc/yum.repos.d/scl.repo'
#yum install python27
Thats it, check the version with the below command  
#python -V

Installing Ipython 
rpm -Uvh http://dl.fedoraproject.org/pub/epel/6/i386/epel-release-6-8.noarch.rpm
yum install ipython
